div.div:
Why Avro ?
==>Apache Avro™ is a data serialization system.

a.xlink:href:
https://app.diagrams.net/

Serialization and deserialization are processes commonly used in computer science to transform data structures or objects into a format that can be easily stored, transmitted, or reconstructed.

1. Serialization

Definition: Serialization is the process of converting a data structure or object into a format that can be easily stored, transmitted, or persisted. The resulting serialized data is often in a standardized, platform-independent format, such as JSON, XML, or binary data.

1.1 Purpose:

  • Data Storage: Serialization is used to save the state of an object or data structure to a file or database.
  • Data Transmission: Serialized data can be sent over a network or between different systems.

1.2 Example:

class Person:
    def __init__(self, name, age):
        self.name = name
        self.age = age

Serialization of a Person object to JSON:

{"name": "John", "age": 25}
